# Generalize the Action Model (Roadmap Item 3)

## Context

The current action model is flat: `DeployAction` and `RevertAction` are simple interfaces with no type discriminant. The executors (`executeDeploy`, `executeRevert`) branch on `action.method` or `stat.isSymbolicLink()` — skill-dir–specific details baked directly into the loop body.

Before the engine can represent file-write or config-patch actions, the model needs a discriminated union so each action kind owns its execution logic. Adding a new kind should require only: define the interface, add it to the union, and add a `case` in the executor. TypeScript's `never` exhaustiveness check enforces this at compile time.

This is a pure structural refactor — no behavior changes, no new features.

---

## Files to Modify

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| `src/types.ts` | Add `kind` discriminant, split into named concrete + union alias |
| `src/core/deploy.ts` | Add `kind: "skill-dir"` in planner; dispatch on `action.kind` in executor |
| `src/core/revert.ts` | Add `kind: "skill-dir"` in both planners; dispatch on `action.kind` in executor |
| `test/deploy.test.ts` | Add `kind: "skill-dir"` to 4 manually-constructed action objects |

---

## Step-by-Step Plan

### 1. `src/types.ts`

Replace the two action interfaces (lines 27–39) with named concrete types and union aliases:

```typescript
export interface SkillDirDeployAction {
  kind: "skill-dir";
  skill: string;
  agent: AgentId;
  source: string;
  target: string;
  method: "symlink" | "copy";
}

// Union-ready: add new action kinds here
export type DeployAction = SkillDirDeployAction;

export interface SkillDirRevertAction {
  kind: "skill-dir";
  skill: string;
  agent: AgentId;
  target: string;
}

// Union-ready: add new action kinds here
export type RevertAction = SkillDirRevertAction;
```

All existing import sites continue to work unchanged (`DeployAction` and `RevertAction` are still exported by the same names).

---

### 2. `src/core/deploy.ts`

**Planner** — add `kind: "skill-dir"` to the `actions.push(...)` call in `planDeploy` (around line 60):

```typescript
actions.push({
  kind: "skill-dir",
  skill: skill.name,
  agent: agentId,
  source,
  target,
  method,
});
```

**Executor** — wrap the `for` loop body in `executeDeploy` with a `switch` on `action.kind`. Existing logic moves verbatim into `case "skill-dir":`. Add exhaustive `default`:

```typescript
for (const action of actions) {
  switch (action.kind) {
    case "skill-dir": {
      const label = `${action.skill} -> ${action.agent}`;
      // ... exact same body as today ...
      break;
    }
    default: {
      const _: never = action;
      throw new Error(`Unhandled deploy action kind: ${JSON.stringify(_)}`);
    }
  }
}
```

No changes to any internal helpers (`executeDeployAction`, `createDeployTarget`, `backupExisting`, `removeTarget`, etc.).

---

### 3. `src/core/revert.ts`

**Planners** — add `kind: "skill-dir"` in both `planRevert` (line 23) and `planRevertAll` (line 42):

```typescript
actions.push({ kind: "skill-dir", skill: skill.name, agent: agentId, target });
```

**Executor** — wrap the `for` loop body in `executeRevert` with a `switch` on `action.kind`. Existing `executeRevertAction` delegation moves into `case "skill-dir":`. Add exhaustive `default`:

```typescript
for (const action of actions) {
  switch (action.kind) {
    case "skill-dir": {
      const result = await executeRevertAction(action, dryRun, verbose, home);
      if (result.outcome === "fail") {
        failed.push({ action, error: result.error });
      } else if (result.outcome === "skip") {
        skipped++;
      } else {
        succeeded++;
      }
      break;
    }
    default: {
      const _: never = action;
      throw new Error(`Unhandled revert action kind: ${JSON.stringify(_)}`);
    }
  }
}
```

`executeRevertAction` signature is unchanged.

---

### 4. `test/deploy.test.ts`

Four manually-constructed `DeployAction` objects need `kind: "skill-dir"` added. All use `method: "copy"`:

- Line 582 (`firstAction`)
- Line 606 (`failAction`)
- Line 782 (`action` — source-immutability test)
- Line 838 (`action` — source-immutability after revert test)

The `registerDeployment` call at line 383 is a registry entry object (not a `DeployAction`) — leave it unchanged.

---

## Reusable Existing Functions

- `executeDeployAction(action, verbose, home)` — `src/core/deploy.ts` — called unchanged from `case "skill-dir"`
- `executeRevertAction(action, dryRun, verbose, home)` — `src/core/revert.ts` — called unchanged from `case "skill-dir"`
- `registerDeployment`, `verifyDeployment` — `src/core/ownership.ts` — unchanged throughout

---

## Files NOT Changed

- `src/index.ts` — uses only public planner/executor API
- `src/core/ownership.ts` — registry format (skill-dir specific) stays as-is
- `src/schemas/registry.ts` — unchanged
- All other test files (`cli`, `cross-platform`, `detect`, `manifest`, `ownership`, `resolve`)

---

## Verification

```bash
npm run build      # Zero TypeScript errors
npm run fmt        # Auto-format any whitespace diffs
npm run lint       # Clean Biome lint
npm test           # All existing tests pass unchanged
```

Focus: `test/deploy.test.ts` and `test/revert.test.ts` — every existing assertion must pass.

